        <h3 style="margin-top: 0px;" id="pop_facts">
            Charleston Population Facts
        </h3>
    


            <h4>What is the current population of Charleston?</h4>
            <p>
                Based on the latest 2022 data from the US census, the
                current population of Charleston is 48,018.  Charleston, West Virginia is the 828th largest city in the US.
            </p>

            
                <h4>What county is Charleston, West Virginia in?</h4>
                <p>
                
                    Charleston is located entirely in 
                    Kanawha County.
                
                </p>
            

            
                
                    <h4>What is the size of Charleston, West Virginia in square miles?</h4>
                    Charleston has an area of 
                    31.5 square miles.

                    
                    
                        Charleston is the
                        
                        largest city, by area, in West Virginia.
                    
                
            

            <h4>What was the peak population of Charleston?</h4>
            <p>
                
                    The peak population of Charleston was in
                    1990, when its population was
                    57,691.
                    
                        In 1990, Charleston was the
                        425th largest city in the US; now
                        its fallen to the 828th largest city in
                        the US.
                    
                    Charleston is currently
                        <span style="color: red;">
                            16.8%
                            smaller
                        </span>
                        than it was in 1990.
                    </p>
                
            </p>
            
                
                    <h4>How quickly is Charleston shrinking?</h4>
                
                <p>
                    
                        Charleston has shrunk
                        9.9% 
                        since the year 2000.
                    


                    
                        Charleston, West Virginia's growth is extremely below
                        average.
                        95% of similarly sized
                        cities are growing faster since 2000.
                    
                </p>
            

            

            
                <h4>What is the population density of Charleston, West Virginia?</h4>
                <p>
                Charleston has a population density of
                1,630.7 people
                per square mile.

                
                
                </p>
            

            

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
