        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="demographics">
            Charleston Demographics
        </h3>
    


            
                

                
                <h4>What is the voting age population of Charleston, West Virginia?</h4>
                <p>
                    The total voting age population of Charleston, West Virginia, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 38,387.  The voting age population is 47.6% male and 52.4% female.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Charleston, West Virginia residents are senior citizens?</h4>
                    <p>
                        According to the latest census statistics, 19.3% of
                        the residents of Charleston are 65 or older.
                    </p>
                

                
                    

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    
                    
                    <h4>What are the racial demographics of Charleston, West Virginia?</h4>
                    <p>The racial demographics of Charleston are 77.9% White, 15.7% Black, 3.7% Two or more races, 2.1% Asian, 0.3% American Indian and 0.2% Other. Additionally, 1.0% of the population identifies as Hispanic.</p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Charleston, West Virginia residents are below the poverty line?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Charleston, 20.9% of
                    residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate
                    is 30.7%.
                    On a per-household basis,
                    16.3% of families are below
                    the poverty line in Charleston.
                    </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Charleston, West Virginia residents are in the labor force?</h4>
                    <p>
                    Among those aged 16 and older, 57.5% of
                    Charleston residents are in the labor force.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                <h4>What are the education levels among Charleston, West Virginia residents?</h4>
                <p>Among the adult population 25 years old and over,
                    91.9% of
                    Charleston residents have at least a high school degree or
                    equivalent, 39.3%
                    have a bachelor's degree and 19.0%
                    have a graduate or professional degree.
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of Charleston, West Virginia residents speak a non-English language at home?</h4>
                <p>
                Among Charleston residents aged 5 and older, 4.5% of them speak a non-English language at home.
                Broken down by language:
                1.0% of residents speak Spanish at home,
                1.7% speak an Indo-European language, and
                0.9% speak an Asian language.

                </p>
                

                
    
        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="labor">
            Charleston Income &amp; Labor Statistics
        </h3>
    


                
                
                    <h4>What is the unemployment rate in Charleston, West Virginia?</h4>
                    <p>
                        The unemployment rate in Charleston is 5.2%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.
                    </p>

                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Charleston, West Virginia residents work for the government?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Charleston, 20.0% of the
                    residents in the non-military labor force 
                    are employed by the local, state and federal government.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                    <h4>What is the median income in Charleston, West Virginia?</h4>
                    <p>The median household income in Charleston is $43,344.</p>
                

                
    
        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="housing">
            Charleston Housing &amp; Rent Statistics
        </h3>
    


                
                
                <h4>What percentage of housing units are owner-occupied in Charleston, West Virginia?</h4>
                <p>
                    In Charleston, 56.6% of housing units
                    are occupied by their owners.
                </p>
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of housing units are rented in Charleston, West Virginia?</h4>
                <p>
                    Renters occupy 43.4% of housing units in
                    Charleston.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Charleston, West Virginia housing units were built before 1940?</h4>
                    <p>
                        Of all the housing units in Charleston,
                        20.6% of them were build before 1940.
                    </p>
                

                
                

                
                    <h4>What percentage of Charleston, West Virginia housing units were built after 2000?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Charleston, 4.5% of the 
                    total housing units were built
                    
                        after the year 2000, which is approximately 
                        
                            1,200 units.
                        
                    
                    </p>
                
                
                
                
                <h4>What is the median monthly rent in Charleston, West Virginia?</h4>
                <p>
                    The median gross monthly rent payment for renters in Charleston is
                    $735.
                </p>

                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of households in Charleston, West Virginia have broadband internet?</h4>
                <p>
                    In Charleston, 77.7% of households have
                    an active broadband internet connection.
                </p>
                
                
            

            

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
